<catsoop-section>What's Happening</catsoop-section>

When you flip a flap from 0 to 1, it adds a value to your total count.

Each bit has a fixed value:
- Bit 0 = 1
- Bit 1 = 2
- Bit 2 = 4
- Bit 3 = 8

When bits flip, computers add these values together to make bigger numbers. This is how binary counting works — it's the language of computers!

